            <Title>The Loss Survivor's Club Orchestra</Title>
            <Text>THE LOSS SURVIVOR’S CABAL ORCHESTRA Features A Live Band - Performers who represent the last survivors of the Loss Town Orchestra, brought into the real world to perform for reasons unknown. Meta Concerns - At first, we will only have time to produce recorded music, after having hinted at the songs throughout the initial release of the project. Eventually, however, I would like to move on to live gigs, with a “manager” character called Wayle, who appears in the game and leaves the Institute to start organising gigs. - There will be clues for fans at the gigs. - They have to be petitioned to get people to perform the songs of the youth, in a ritualistic fashion, every time they gig. - Players may be able to act as security at a gig for an in-game benefit. Downloads - The music, when available, is free to anyone who has spent any Nex on the game. Aesthetic - Smartly dressed. - They wear masks, influenced by the artwork of the town. Influences Qawwali - Devotional, droning, very long, a trance state. Body Percussion - Using oneself as an instrument. This ties into the mythology of town, and the representation of the townsfolk in art. Repetition - Ritualism is key here.</Text>
