            <Text>A small painting in a cheap frame. Description The painting, perhaps produced by a simpleton or child, depicts a beach scene, a cobbled road leading through an arch, and flowered meadows, to a wide sea. The foreground is in shadow, as if something is behind the painter. Attached to it by string is a luggage label, which when clicked reads: Sir And Magus, My spawn sends her regards and apologises for the incident yesterday. She will be beaten, as per your request. Please accept this gift from both of us. Safe Travels, Death In Strange Light March 16th If the reader clicks the four metal clasps on the back the frame comes apart, and they will find a scrap of fabric, stitched with mountain flowers: it is the same material that Death of a Friend is wearing in photographs of her. In spilled ink, with a pained hand, is a small devotive message: I forgive you. I am your pet. Sometimes we must kick a dog.</Text>
