            <Text>The Only Loss Curriculous For The Bright-Eyed Deep Are Our Pockets, That We May Finger Our Coins In Secret (The school's motto is repeated in the Tachygraph) APPARITION REGISTER Teacher's Name:................Apples Like Young Lungs...................................... Note To Teachers: Please Write Student's Full Name, Including Prelux NOTE ANY ABSENCES IN RED INK AND FORWARD TO THE SCHOOL MASTER Name Age Week 1 Week 2 Week 3 Week 4 Week 5 Week 6 Week 7 Week 8 Week 9 Comments Father Shot In Leg 9 x o o o o x x x x Father is often ill from school; his mother writes of his tinnitus and vertigo in her diary. He did manage a few days in each week, though by Week 6 he was ill, as expected, and we have not heard from his mother. Hopefully the vertigo. Drunk At Christmas 10 o o x o o x x o x Drunk is a bully and a truant, and his attendance was erratic. Towards the end of term he came to school haggard and increasingly ill, and the Lead Augur had no choice but to send him home for fear of infection. We believed it was he who had stolen the desks. Cousin's Kiss 9 o O x O O O O O x Cousin missed several days in the middle of term, though fears were allayed as she is still with us, despite being missing last week because of a punctured liver. Hand In Trousers 10 O O O O O X X X X Hand came into school in Week 3 with ugly bruises around his head; this was before the Town Order had notified us of any danger. We kept him in for a few weeks, but had to quarantine him as soon as we knew. Joy At Violence 10 O x O O X X X X X There are rumours of domestic violence and god worship at her home; the reason for her absence could be disease or abuse. It is not for us to say. Squeamish In The Face Of Dry Hands Rubbing 10 O O x O x x O X X Squeamish seemed to overcome his blight, after he contracted it, the symptoms disappearing and he was sporadically allowed back into the classroom. We heard he had relapsed, and his death was quietly announced last week. Book Burnt For Secrets 9 O O X X X X X X X The Mayor removed his son at the first possible juncture; I can only hope for his safety. The efficacy of my teaching, and the well-being of the others, has obviously improved with his absence. Gagging On Wooden Spoon 11 O X X X X X X X x Gagging, and her parents, have not been seen in town for months. Their home was abandoned, and was demolished last week. The roads are all lined with torches. First Bath In Winter 10 O O X X X X X X x First Bath was one of the early victims; his desk was turned to the back of the class, by one of the other children. Nobody will admit to it. Spiders Crawl On Him 9 x x x x x x x x x N/A (Line Crossed Through The Entire Entry) Dreams Of Royalty 9 X X O X X X X X x Dreams has left to be home-tutored; we hope that she is safe. Her father brought her schoolbooks back and tied them to the gates. Scatterbird Caught Alone 9 O X X X X X X X X Scatterbird and Spiders were best friends and neighbours, and so the call that he had passed on came as no surprise. I have now learnt that the desks were taken by him, over a period of weeks. I went to his cremation, and saw the nest; it stretched between his home and the window of the house next door, where they had already demolished a room. It had been Spiders', and in the remnants of the webbing I could see the two desks, interlocked.</Text>
            <Notes>No, it is not. LA In what way is this pertinent to the report? Superstition is not part of your job. LA Miss Lungs, this is above and beyond your role here at the Curriculous. Please come and see me. I shall be at the river, walking.</Notes>
