            <Title>Artwork Introduction</Title>
            <Text>ARTWORK Unified Features A WIDE VARIETY The breadth of artwork in this piece is quite large, from the traditional to the outsider, from the symbolic to the informative - graphs, paintings, sketches, drawings, diagrams, woodcuts, maps, photographs and more. This list will grow when and if the project is successful. They will be crafted (in the fiction) by many different hands, at a number of different times. This variety must be evident. VERNACULAR DETAIL Incidental detail, and symbolism, even in the most mundane of pieces, is what will bring them to life. Readers will already be in the mode of analysis. As well as striking them with beauty, the pieces should add to the richness of the town and the characters, and lead them to new revelations. A NEW STYLE This is something that I need to work on, but the town needs a new style that works with its peculiarity. It will take tropes of classical art and subvert them, and superficially present a very alien view of human life. Elements such as holding animals (this time at arm’s length), spiral designs, titillation, pictures of the gods (in pathetic poses) EVIDENCE These pieces, like the writing and 3D models, are evidence, and should bear the marks of travel and handling - stains, blemishes, etc. These can even be part of the puzzle that they present.</Text>
