Their illness does not incapacitate them, but allows them to travel. The fact that they are infectious is not often 

His Relationship With Disease

- It is part of him, and is infused in him. He cannot be cured.
- The miasma is tied to sea winds, and his desire for the sea can be attributed to it. He is allowed to take off his mask when he is in a boat, and perhaps infects the entirety of the world. 
- The Miasma, in Latin, is “nebula”, and should be tied to his love of stars.
- He is a little like the Pied Piper, and this comparison should necessarily be lost. 
- Coincidentally, because of his mop suit full of charcoal, he is scared of fire, and keeps away from it. 

His Relationship With Writing

- The “high-falutin’” language is a smokescreen - he is in fact a plain writer, and a liar.
- He is better at drawing animals.

His Relationship With Travelling

- He is called “The Stiff One” - he is so tightly bandaged as he is travelling so much. 
